{
  "texts": [
    "(Kaur et al., 2022) One typical challenge that illustrates the need is bias propagation.",
    "When a biased or incorrect piece of information is introduced by either the KG or the LLM and is subsequently reinforced through iterative reasoning, the system may amplify misleading content without awareness (Bender et al., 2021).",
    "This not only compromises factual correctness but also undermines user trust, especially in domains such as healthcare, education, or law.",
    "Imagine a knowledge graph encodes historical associations such as \"CEO-typically male.\"",
    "After integrating historical data based patterns into LLM, LLM may output content such as \"He is a natural leader and would excel as a CEO.\""
  ]
}